title: Locally compact space
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

A topological space $$X$$ is called //locally compact,// if every point $$x\in X$$ has a compact neighbourhood, i.e. there exist an open set $$U$$ and a compact set $$K$$ with $$x\in U\subseteq K.$$